{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% set honest = card_data.managers.honest %}
{% set overlaid = card_data.managers.overlaid %}
{% set comp = overlaid.screen.composite %}
{% set gate = overlaid.screen.power_gate %}

{% macro diag_label(name) %}{{ {
  "treynor_mazuy": "Treynor–Mazuy γ (curvature)",
  "updown_beta": "Up/down β gap (β⁺ − β⁻)",
  "market_coskew": "Market coskewness",
  "drawdown_vol": "Drawdown vs vol signature",
  "straddle_loading": "Fung–Hsieh straddle loading"
}[name] }}{% endmacro %}

{% macro verdict_token(v) %}{{ "shrink" if v == "short-vol-consistent" else ("noise" if v in ["inconclusive", "not-played"] else "robust") }}{% endmacro %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/m2.css">
{% endblock %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="m2-intro">
  <p class="m2-headline">
    Two synthetic managers, one market, {{ card_data.meta.months }} months, tier
    {{ card_data.meta.tier }}. <strong>{{ honest.name }}</strong> and
    <strong>{{ overlaid.name }}</strong> report the <em>same</em> Sharpe to two
    decimals ({{ "%.2f"|format(honest.sharpe.point) }}) &mdash; but one is quietly
    short volatility. The convexity screen reads payoff <em>shape</em>, not the
    average, so it separates them where every linear statistic cannot.
  </p>
  <aside class="m2-disclosure" role="note">
    The overlaid book's written-put premium is calibrated in-sample and set
    <strong>rich of fair</strong> &mdash; above the actuarial cost of its
    payouts &mdash; so both books report the same healthy Sharpe: the classic
    carry seduction, where selling insurance above cost flatters every
    average-based statistic. That calibration is a deliberate look-ahead for a
    controlled demonstration and <strong>not a claim about live methodology</strong>
    &mdash; a real short-vol book's premium is set ex-ante. The atlas detection
    rows are measured at <strong>fair premium</strong> (zero in-sample carry),
    the conservative case. Fully synthetic; manager names are fictional.
  </aside>
</section>

<section class="m2-pair">
  {% for key, m in [("honest", honest), ("overlaid", overlaid)] %}
  <article class="m2-manager m2-manager--{{ key }}">
    <h2 class="m2-manager__name">{{ m.name }}</h2>
    <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="sharpe"
         data-lo="{{ m.sharpe.ci_lo }}" data-point="{{ m.sharpe.point }}" data-hi="{{ m.sharpe.ci_hi }}">
      <span class="interval-stat__label">Reported Sharpe</span>
      <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%.2f"|format(m.sharpe.point) }}</span>
      <div class="interval-stat__rail"><div class="interval-stat__band"></div><div class="interval-stat__point"></div></div>
      <span class="interval-stat__range">95% interval {{ "%.2f"|format(m.sharpe.ci_lo) }} &hellip; {{ "%.2f"|format(m.sharpe.ci_hi) }}</span>
    </div>
    <span class="verdict-chip m2-composite" data-verdict="{{ m.screen.composite.chip }}">{{ m.screen.composite.label }}</span>
    <p class="m2-tally">{{ m.screen.composite.short_vol_count }} of {{ m.screen.composite.playable_count }} playable diagnostics short-vol-consistent (flag at {{ m.screen.composite.k }}).</p>
  </article>
  {% endfor %}
</section>

<section class="m2-diagnostics">
  <h2 class="m2-section__title">Four windows onto one shape &mdash; {{ overlaid.name }}</h2>
  <p class="m2-note">Converging evidence, not a p-value. Each diagnostic reads the same left-tail geometry; the tally is agreement across windows, never a manufactured joint significance.</p>
  {% for name, d in overlaid.screen.diagnostics.items() %}
  {% if d.played %}
  <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="{{ name }}"
       data-lo="{{ d.ci_lo }}" data-point="{{ d.point }}" data-hi="{{ d.ci_hi }}"
       data-verdict="{{ verdict_token(d.verdict) }}">
    <span class="interval-stat__label">{{ diag_label(name) }}</span>
    <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%+.3f"|format(d.point) }}</span>
    <div class="interval-stat__rail"><div class="interval-stat__band"></div><div class="interval-stat__point"></div></div>
    <span class="interval-stat__range">90% interval {{ "%+.3f"|format(d.ci_lo) }} &hellip; {{ "%+.3f"|format(d.ci_hi) }} &mdash; {{ d.verdict }}</span>
  </div>
  {% else %}
  <div class="power-gate m2-rung-unplayed">
    <span class="power-gate__title">{{ diag_label(name) }}</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason">Rung unplayed: requires the external Fung&ndash;Hsieh PTFS straddle series (public; adapter not yet built). The demo never fabricates it.</p>
  </div>
  {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
  <p class="m2-downleg-note">The up/down β gap is a <strong>static payoff-shape descriptor</strong>, never a conditional-alpha table. Its down-leg is identified off ~19 down-months at T = 48, so its interval is honestly wide.</p>
</section>

{% if not gate.open %}
<section class="m2-powergate">
  <div class="power-gate">
    <span class="power-gate__title">power gate</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason">{{ gate.reason }}</p>
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

<section class="m2-stress">
  <h2 class="m2-section__title">Stress-month receipts</h2>
  <p class="m2-note">The months the written put paid out &mdash; identical books until the tail arrives.</p>
  <svg class="m2-stress-strip" viewBox="0 0 100 30" preserveAspectRatio="none" role="img" aria-label="Honest vs overlaid monthly returns"></svg>
  <table class="m2-stress-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Month</th><th>Market</th><th>{{ honest.name }}</th><th>{{ overlaid.name }}</th><th>Put payout</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for s in card_data.stress_months %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ s.month }}</td>
        <td>{{ "%+.1f"|format(s.market_factor * 100) }}%</td>
        <td>{{ "%+.1f"|format(s.honest_return * 100) }}%</td>
        <td class="m2-stress-hit">{{ "%+.1f"|format(s.overlaid_return * 100) }}%</td>
        <td>&minus;{{ "%.1f"|format(s.payout * 100) }}%</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>Five returns-based convexity diagnostics over a de-smoothed return series: a
Treynor&ndash;Mazuy quadratic term, a Henriksson&ndash;Merton up/down β gap,
Harvey&ndash;Siddique market coskewness, a drawdown-vs-vol signature (reusing the
S2 drawdown band read for asymmetry), and &mdash; where the external Fung&ndash;Hsieh
straddle series is loaded &mdash; a PTFS loading. Each is a single static shape
coefficient over the whole window, interval-reported by a circular block
bootstrap; none is a regime split or a time-varying beta.</p>
<p>The composite is an <em>evidence tally</em>, not a score and not a p-value: it
flags <em>investigate</em> only when at least {{ comp.k }} playable diagnostics
agree in the short-vol direction and the power gate for this track length is
open. De-smoothing first is the load-bearing false-alarm control &mdash; it keeps
an honest-but-smooth illiquid book from being mistaken for a short-vol one.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/m2-convexity.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
